      "id": "RQ-0024",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Centralize supported-runner wording in docs and schema",
      "description": "Principles violated: C) DRY knowledge, G) Least astonishment, J) Consistency/Integrity. The source supports Kimi, Pi, and plugin runner IDs, but multiple config docs and schema descriptions still list only Codex/OpenCode/Gemini/Claude/Cursor. Users relying on editor schema help or config docs can incorrectly conclude newer runners are unsupported. Minimal fix: update the Rust doc comments that generate schema descriptions plus stale docs, and prefer one canonical supported-runner wording.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "docs",
        "schema",
        "runner"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "docs/configuration.md",
        "docs/guides/advanced.md",
        "schemas/config.schema.json",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/agent.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/runner.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: docs/configuration.md:37 :: config example says choose from codex, opencode, gemini, claude, cursor.",
        "path: docs/guides/advanced.md:539 :: advanced guide repeats the stale runner list.",
        "path: schemas/config.schema.json:8 :: schema description says Agent runner defaults are Claude, Codex, OpenCode, Gemini, or Cursor.",
        "path: schemas/config.schema.json:188 :: nested schema repeats the stale runner description.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/mod.rs:74 :: Rust doc comment feeding schema omits Kimi, Pi, and plugin runners.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/agent.rs:79 :: AgentConfig doc comment also omits Kimi, Pi, and plugin runners.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/runner.rs:45 :: Runner::Kimi serializes to kimi.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/contracts/runner.rs:46 :: Runner::Pi serializes to pi.",
        "workflow: rg -n \"codex, opencode, gemini, claude, cursor|Agent runner defaults|Runner::Kimi|Runner::Pi\" docs schemas/config.schema.json crates/ralph/src/contracts :: showed stale docs/schema alongside source support for Kimi and Pi."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Update Rust doc comments on config agent defaults to include codex, opencode, gemini, claude, cursor, kimi, pi, and plugin runner IDs.",
        "Update docs/configuration.md and docs/guides/advanced.md examples to use the same canonical wording.",
        "Regenerate schemas/config.schema.json from source rather than hand-editing generated output.",
        "Add or update a schema/doc alignment test for the supported runner list if practical.",
        "Verify by running make generate and rg for the stale partial runner list."
      ],
