      "id": "RQ-0025",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Update session cache path references to session.jsonc",
      "description": "Principles violated: G) Least astonishment, H) Operational hygiene, J) Consistency/Integrity. Runtime code and tests use .ralph/cache/session.jsonc, but several operator docs and AGENTS guidance still reference .ralph/cache/session.json. That sends users and agents to delete or inspect the wrong file during resume recovery and parallel-worker cleanup. Minimal fix: replace stale session.json references with session.jsonc and add a lightweight docs/search guard for this path.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "docs",
        "session",
        "recovery"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "AGENTS.md",
        "docs/workflow.md",
        "docs/features/phases.md",
        "docs/guides/advanced.md",
        "crates/ralph/src/session/persistence.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/constants.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
